claim.claim-text:
19 In a wideband radio system, a receiver, said receiver adapted to detect wideband burst signals, said wideband burst signals having a time spacing, comprising: 
a means for generating local signals, said local signals being substantially similar to said received signals; 
a means for generating a product signal responsive to said received signals and to said local signals, said product signal being the product of one of said received signals and one of said local signals; 
a means for synchronizing the occurrence of said one of said local signals with one of said received signals, said means for synchronizing being responsive to said product signal and having an output, said output being provided to said means for generating local signals; and 
an integrator means responsive to said product signal.
